<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The Zend_Validate_Int validator does not correctly handle boolean input values:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$value = true; // Not a number at all!
$validator = new Zend_Validate_Int();
$result = $validator-&gt;isValid($value);
</code></pre>

<p>The $result variable has been "(bool)true" after the call to isValid(). With setting $value to "false", $result changed to "false" too.</p>

